Orthodox Christians Observe Easter Amid Crackdown On Rogue Priests And CongregantsEnlarge this image toggle caption Sergei Grits/AP Sergei Grits/APUpdated at 12:34 p.m.
But the coronavirus pandemic has shut down those celebrations in many Orthodox Christian countries, including Greece, Romania and Serbia.
Police are monitoring streets by drone and patrolling outside churches to make sure priests holding closed-door services do not let in parishioners.
Prime Minister Kyriakos Mitsotakis banned church services last month, after weeks of pushback from the Greek Orthodox Church.
But some Greek Orthodox priests have balked.